<para>
  This command creates a new empty &micro; with no associated
  &images;.  To create a &micro; with an &image;, see <xref
  linkend='MenuItem-OOF.Microstructure.Create_From_Image'/> or <xref
  linkend='MenuItem-OOF.Microstructure.Create_From_ImageFile'/>.  To
  create a &micro; from an <link
  linkend="Section-Concepts-Microstructure-OrientationMap">ebsd
  orientation map</link>, see <xref
  linkend="MenuItem-OOF.Microstructure.Create_From_OrientationMap_File"/>.
</para>
<para>
  If the value of the <varname>name</varname> argument is <link
  linkend="Object-automatic"><userinput>automatic</userinput></link>,
  the &micro; will be named <quote>microstructure</quote>.  If a
  &micro; already exists with the given name,
  <userinput>&lt;x&gt;</userinput> will be appended to it, where
  <userinput>x</userinput> is an integer chosen to make the name
  <link linkend="Section-Concepts-Path-Unique">unique</link>. 
</para>

